        <p class="byline-block__review">Reviewed by a QuickBooks ProAdvisor &middot; independent, no reseller incentive</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="qbcost-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Written fixed fee &middot; free review first &middot; no commission</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How we price &mdash; and who quotes it</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stat-row">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div><div class="stat__value">{{ s.value }}</div><div class="stat__label">{{ s.label }}</div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcost-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What a QuickBooks ProAdvisor costs, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p id="qbcost-in-brief-text">{{ inBrief.text | safe }}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcost-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">ProAdvisor cost, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcost-fixed">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How we price</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Written fixed fee, not hourly &mdash; and why.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to a flat figure &mdash; a fixed monthly fee for ongoing work, or a flat project fee for a cleanup or setup &mdash; agreed in writing before any work starts. Three reasons we don&rsquo;t bill hourly.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for w in whyFixed %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ w.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ w.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcost-factors">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What drives the cost</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six factors that move your fee within the range.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">There is no single flat price because no two files are the same. These six factors do most of the work in deciding where a quote lands &mdash; more of any of them moves the fee toward the top of the range; a clean, current, simple file sits at the bottom.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for f in factors %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcost-ranges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Cost by engagement type</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What each engagement ranges from &mdash; and to.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">These are our canonical starting ranges, always shown as a range and never as a single point. They&rsquo;re estimates, not quotes &mdash; your exact fixed fee is set in writing after the free file review. The <a href="/pricing/">pricing page</a> is the authoritative list; this section summarizes the engagements and what drives each one.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for r in ranges %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ r.engagement | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ r.range | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ r.basis | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><strong>What moves it:</strong> {{ r.drives | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><a href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.link | safe }} &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="section__lede">Every figure above is an estimate, not a quote &mdash; the exact fixed fee is set in writing after a free discovery call and file review. The QuickBooks software subscription is billed by Intuit separately; current subscription pricing is on Intuit&rsquo;s site. We earn no commission on QuickBooks subscriptions.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcost-scenarios">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Representative scenarios</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three illustrations of how the factors land.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">These are illustrative scenarios to show how the cost factors combine &mdash; not averages, not client data, and not quotes. Your figure is fixed in writing after the file review.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in scenarios %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcost-routing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Your next step</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How do you want to get your number?</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="buyer-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ b.opener | safe }}</p><p class="buyer-card__body">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">{{ b.cta | safe }}</span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcost-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How the pricing is set</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed-fee, scoped to your file. Independent. No commission.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A QuickBooks ProAdvisor&rsquo;s fee is only honest if it reflects the actual work. That&rsquo;s why we don&rsquo;t publish a single flat price and don&rsquo;t bill hourly: we review the file first, scope the work to the real drivers &mdash; condition, backlog, volume, accounts, integrations, product tier, and entity structure &mdash; and quote one written fixed fee within our canonical ranges. You see the number, and what it covers, before anything begins, and the fee only changes if the scope genuinely changes.</p>
      <p>We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; no Intuit affiliate revenue, no commissions &mdash; so the scope and the fee reflect what your books need, not what keeps you on a more expensive plan. The QuickBooks software subscription is billed by Intuit separately. You can see the <a href="/pricing/">full pricing list</a>, <a href="/tools/bookkeeping-cost-calculator/">estimate your range</a>, or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbcost-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Cost questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask about ProAdvisor cost.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qbcost-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qbcost-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-19</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-19</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-19 &middot; QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbcost-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Pricing, the calculator, and where to start.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
